column3: Concealed carry permits issued to residents? (2 if permit not needed for CC, 1 if yes, 0 if no)
column4: Concealed carry permits issued to nonresidents? (2 if permit not needed for CC, 1 if yes,.5 if yes for property owners/employed in state/may issue, 0 if no)
column5: Concealed carry permits are shall-issue? (2 if permit not needed, 1 if yes, 0.5 if theoretically yes but broad exceptions exist or theoretically may issue but effectively more like shall issue, 0 if no)
column6: Training or testing requirement for carry permit (1=yes/no permits, 0=no/may carry without permit)
column7: Initial permit cost in dollars, excluding training costs (n/a if no permits issued, 0 if permits not required)
column8: Consumer Price Index, All Items, Annual
column9: Initial permit cost in 2006 dollars (twice the maximum cost in any other state if no permits issued, 0 if permits not required)
column10: Initial permit term (0 if no permits issued, 25 if permits not required)
column11: Is loaded handgun carry permitted in bars, banks, casinos, hospitals, places of worship, public demonstrations, parks, and athletic events? (1=yes, 0=no)
column12: Open carry of loaded handgun (permitted without permit=2, permitted with permit=1, not generally permitted=0)
column13: Carry in motor vehicles (peaceable journey) (3=no restrictions even if concealed, 2= either “plain view” or “concealed” restrictions, 1=only with concealed carry permit (unless in locked container or glove box), 0.5=permitted with CC permit/license but only if in plain view, 0=not permitted unless locked in container)
column14: State preemption of local open carry ordinances? (1=yes, 0.5=limited/special legislation for particular localities, 0=no)
column15: State preemption of local concealed carry ordinances? (1=yes, 0.5=limited/special legislation for particular localities, 0=no)
column16: Open carry index (see "Carry indices" page for construction)
column17: Concealed carry index (see “Carry indices” page for construction)
column21: Local gun ban in place? (1=sale & possession, 0.5=sale only, 0=none)
column22: Non powder guns' use or possession regulated? (1=yes, 0.5=locally, 0=no or just deals with young minors)
column23: Stricter minimum age to purchase or possess firearms than federal standard? (1=yes, 0=no)
column24: Waiting period on firearms purchases? (1=all firearms, 0.5=some firearms, 0=no)
column26: Licensing or regulation of gun dealers? (1=yes, 0.5=locally or only warning to purchasers, 0=no)

column32: Licensing or permitting of gun owners or purchasers? (1=all guns, 0.5=handguns only, 0=no; multiplied by 0.5 if locally only)
column35: Registration of firearms? (1=all firearms, 0.5=some firearms, 0=no – multiplied by 0.5 if locally only)
column36: Design safety standards for handguns ("Saturday night special" ban)? (1=yes, 0=no)
column37: Built-in locking devices required? (2=yes and must be stored in a locked container or with lock in place, 1=yes with sale, 0=no)
column38: Child access prevention laws? column41: Law specifying no duty to retreat before using deadly force? (1=yes, applying everywhere, 0.75 home & vehicle, 0.5=only in home (aka castle doctrine), 0=none)
